
Terraform is a Infrastructure as a code 

Terraform architecture

init  
validate
fmt
plan
apply
destroy


Terraform workflow 

write--->Init--->plan--->apply--->destroy

developer writes .tf files
       |
       |
terraform init
       |
       |
providers downloaded
       |
       |
terraform plan
       |
       |
authentication with cloud
       |
       |
terraform apply
       |
       |
state updated 

StateFile:-  terraform.tfstate

remote backend storage -S3,blob

s3---store state
state locking -- prevent parallel execution

if process crashes manually remove lock 

terraform force-unlock <LOCK_ID>


in real world .pem file is stored based on environment 

Development / Testing Environments

The .pem file is stored locally on the engineer’s machine:
~/.ssh/devops-key.pem

